headlines.description: Hamidou Diallo scored 15 second-half points, most of them during an 18-0 run, and No. 5 Kentucky shot 59 percent after halftime to rally past Utah Valley 73-63 on Friday night in the opener for both schools.
headlines.shortLinkText: Big second half lifts No. 5 Kentucky past Utah Valley 73-63

video.headline: Kentucky needs big run to beat Utah Valley

headlines.description: Senior Darral Willis scored 19 points to lead No. 7 Wichita State past Missouri-Kansas City 109-57 in its season opener Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 7 Wichita State blows past Missouri-Kansas City 109-57.

headlines.description: Scottie Lindsey scored 26 points, Derek Pardon added 16 and No. 19 Northwestern held off Loyola (Md.) 79-75 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lindsey scores 26 points as Northwestern beats Loyola (Md.)

headlines.description: Michal Cekovsky hit every shot he put up, scoring 10 points to help lead Maryland to a 76-61 win over Stony Brook in the season opener on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland rolls to 76-61 win over Stony Brook in opener

headlines.description: Justin Kier made two free throws with six seconds remaining to give George Mason a 67-65 win over Lafayette in the season opener on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kier's late FTs gives George Mason 67-65 win over Lafayette

headlines.description: Ike Smith had 18 points including the winning free throws with 3.9 seconds left as Georgia Southern shocked Wake Forest 85-83 on Friday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith hits winning FT, Georgia Southern shocks Wake Forest

headlines.description: Yuta Watanabe had 19 points and 11 rebounds and George Washington held off a late run to beat Howard 84-75 in the season opener for both teams on Friday night.
Zac Cuthbertson scored 22 points in just 16 minutes of action as Costal Carolina drubbed Piedmont International 102-50 in the season opener Friday night.
Freshman Dedric Boyd sank three free throws with five seconds left to help Eastern Kentucky beat Rice 73-72 on Friday night in a season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Freshman Boyd hits late FTs, EKU beats Rice 73-72

notes.headline: MGM RESORTS MAIN EVENT - CAMPUS GAME

headlines.description: Jordan Allen scored 21 points, including 5 of 12 3-pointers, and Rider surged in the second half to beat Hampton 90-75 in Friday night's season opener for both teams.
Godwin Boahen scored 15 points and Tarkus Ferguson added 13 to help lead Illinois-Chicago to a 65-55 win over North Carolina Central on the opening night of the season for both teams on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boahen, Ferguson lead UIC to 65-55 win over NCCU

headlines.description: Hayden Dalton scored a career-high 30 points and grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Wyoming to a 74-65 victory over Chattanooga in a season opener on Friday night.
Barry Ogalue scored 20 points, Gabe Levin had 14 points and eight rebounds, and Long Beach State beat San Francisco 83-71 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ogalue scores 20, Long Beach State tops San Francisco 83-71

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
